More than 2500 dogs, representing 138 breeds, will compete for prizes at Sunday's All Breed Dog Show and Obedience Trials at the Los Angeles Sports Arena.  to 9 p. Other attractions include the appearance of Warren Eckstein, radio host of Pet Show, who will answer behavioral questions about dogs (as well as cats, pigs and goldfish, if he's asked); free veterinary advice; a demonstration of how 4-H youngsters help train puppies to become guide dogs, and more than 70 vendors selling dog paraphernalia. Between judgings, a troupe of Dobermans will jump through hoops and barrels and will scale walls. 